# Button Components

## NEVER Use Raw Buttons with Inline Styles

Always use the shared `Button` component from `@/components/shared`. Never use raw `<button>` elements with duplicated inline classes.

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG - raw button with duplicated classes
<button
  onClick={handleClick}
  className="px-4 py-2 text-sm font-ui bg-scripture-accent text-scripture-bg rounded-lg hover:bg-scripture-accent/90 transition-colors"
>
  Save
</button>

<button
  onClick={handleCancel}
  className="px-4 py-2 text-sm font-ui bg-scripture-elevated text-scripture-text rounded-lg hover:bg-scripture-border/50 transition-colors"
>
  Cancel
</button>

// ✅ CORRECT - use shared Button component
import { Button } from '@/components/shared';

<Button variant="primary" onClick={handleClick}>
  Save
</Button>

<Button variant="secondary" onClick={handleCancel}>
  Cancel
</Button>
```

## Available Variants

| Variant | Use For | Appearance |
|---------|---------|------------|
| `primary` | Main actions (Save, Create, Confirm) | Accent background, light text |
| `secondary` | Alternative actions (Cancel, Back) | Elevated background, border |
| `destructive` | Dangerous actions (Delete, Remove) | Red background, white text |
| `ghost` | Subtle actions, toolbars | Muted background, blends in |

```tsx
<Button variant="primary">Save Changes</Button>
<Button variant="secondary">Cancel</Button>
<Button variant="destructive">Delete</Button>
<Button variant="ghost">More Options</Button>
```

## Available Sizes

| Size | Use For | Padding |
|------|---------|---------|
| `sm` | Compact UI, inline actions, toolbars | `px-3 py-1.5 text-sm` |
| `md` | Default, most buttons | `px-4 py-2 text-sm` |
| `lg` | Prominent CTAs, modals | `px-6 py-3 text-base` |

```tsx
<Button size="sm">Small</Button>
<Button size="md">Medium (default)</Button>
<Button size="lg">Large</Button>
```

## Component Props

All `Button` props:
- `variant` - Visual style (default: `'primary'`)
- `size` - Button size (default: `'md'`)
- `fullWidth` - Whether button spans full width
- `disabled` - Disables the button with reduced opacity
- All standard HTML button attributes (`onClick`, `type`, `aria-label`, etc.)

## Common Patterns

### Action Button Pairs
```tsx
<div className="flex gap-2">
  <Button variant="secondary" onClick={onCancel}>Cancel</Button>
  <Button variant="primary" onClick={onSave}>Save</Button>
</div>
```

### Destructive Confirmation
```tsx
<div className="flex gap-2">
  <Button variant="secondary" onClick={onCancel}>Cancel</Button>
  <Button variant="destructive" onClick={onDelete}>Delete</Button>
</div>
```

### Full Width in Forms
```tsx
<Button variant="primary" fullWidth type="submit">
  Create Account
</Button>
```

## When NOT to Use Button

Some cases require custom styling:
- **Icon-only buttons** in toolbars (use `<button>` with custom classes)
- **Toggle/chip buttons** that show selected state (e.g., filter chips)
- **Buttons inside HTML template strings** (can't use React components)

For these cases, follow the theme variables pattern:
```tsx
// Icon-only button
<button
  onClick={onClose}
  className="p-1 text-scripture-muted hover:text-scripture-text transition-colors"
  aria-label="Close"
>
  ✕
</button>

// Toggle/chip button with active state
<button
  className={`px-3 py-1.5 text-sm rounded-lg transition-colors
    ${isActive 
      ? 'bg-scripture-accent text-scripture-bg' 
      : 'bg-scripture-elevated text-scripture-text hover:bg-scripture-border/50'}`}
>
  {label}
</button>
```

## Accessibility

The Button component automatically provides:
- `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-scripture-accent` focus styling
- `focus:ring-offset-2` for visibility
- Proper disabled state with `cursor-not-allowed`
- Inherits `aria-label` and other ARIA attributes
